pull_request.title: Add more vision datasets.
pull_request.body:
### Description

This PR adds scripts to download several commonly used few-shot learning vision datasets, including:

* FC100,
* tiered-ImageNet,
* VGG Flowers, and
* FGVC Aircraft.

For the first two, we replicate the original splits of the authors.
For the latter two, we replicate the splits of Meta-Dataset (Triantafillou et al, 2020).

All implementations include docs and tests.

### Contribution Checklist

If your contribution modifies code in the core library (not docs, tests, or examples), please fill the following checklist.

- [x] My contribution modifies code in the main library.
- [x] My modifications are tested.
- [x] My modifications are documented.

issue.title: [Feature Request] Add metaworld support
issue.body:
Hi!
Thank you for learn2learn!

It would be great to have the support of Metaworld environments (it is pretty tricky right now and requires to change some source code). I'd be happy to help.

comment.body:
Hello @Guitaricet,

Thanks for the kind words! We would love to have support for Meta-World in leaarn2learn, but no one is working on it right now. I think a reasonable approach is to first have a working implementation for a single environment, and to scale that up to the 10 tasks setting following the existing MAML implementation.

If you're interested in contributing an integration of meta-world, feel free to join our slack and we can discuss details there: [slack.learn2learn.net](http://slack.learn2learn.net)

Cheers,
- Séb

issue.title: AttributeError: module 'learn2learn.text.datasets' has no attribute 'TaskGenerator'
issue.body:
Hi,

I am trying to run the news_topic_classification.py in the text examples folder, but I keep running into the error mentioned here:

`Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "news_topic_classification.py", line 166, in <module>
    download_location=args.download_location)
  File "news_topic_classification.py", line 84, in main
    train_gen = l2l.text.datasets.TaskGenerator(text_train, ways=ways)
AttributeError: module 'learn2learn.text.datasets' has no attribute 'TaskGenerator'`

 I am using a conda venv with the following pip list:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30308873/71574767-3791e200-2b10-11ea-9c16-25452bf7da1b.png)

comment.body: Thanks for reporting the bug, fixed in #104.

* Update travis and some deps.

* Fix RandomClassRotations with torchvision==0.5.0.

* try-except for random rotations.

* Remove bare exception.

* th -> torch

* Fix transform issue.

* Add CHANGELOG.md.

* Update travis testing platforms.

* Remove testing with PY38 since not compatible with torch==1.1.0
